- main_bulb: Main Load (lamp) [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- internal_bulb: Internal Indicator Lamp [inside enclosure: cube_load] [NOTE: This lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.]
- load_diode: Load Protection Diode [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: With the new good battery installed and all modules still connected, measure the voltage between the PSU negative output and each inter‑module junction in sequence: (1) at the output pair of Control Module 1, (2) after Module 2, … up to the input of the load module. Record the voltage at each point with all switches ON. This will localize where the 12 V disappears (indicating an open switch path, mis‑wired cable pair, or internal open in a specific control module).
