ACTION:
Disconnect only Control Module 2 from the chain. Using the PSU as source, identify which two terminals on Module 2 are internally continuous when the switch is ON (the intended 12 V through‑path). Then, with all modules powered, individually probe each of the four cables at the Module‑2 interfaces with respect to PSU negative to determine which cable is actually carrying 12 V into Module 2 and which cable (if any) carries 12 V out. This will distinguish between an internal open in Module 2’s switch path and a mis‑wired/swapped cable pair around Module 2.
